fields.Dialogue Text: "LISTEN TO YOUR LITTLE FRIEND. HE IS WISE IN HIS CHILDLIKE WAY. HIS MYSTERIOUS RACE MAY YET PROVE FIERCE COMPETITION TO MY HEROIC HAPLOGROUP."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "He would be appreciative if you did..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He would be appreciative if you did not further chase this line of inquire in front of the women.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""He will grant us three wishes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "He will grant us three wishes."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THE SIZE OF THE EAR LOBES IS NOT A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE SIZE OF THE EAR LOBES IS NOT A REAL CRANIOMETRIC CRITERIA. EVERYONE KNOWS THIS."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "That's understandable. Jean-Luc Mea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's understandable. Jean-Luc Measurehead is a sage and an intellectual giant of race theory. Who are you? Handmaiden of Al Gul.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""I KNEW YOU WOULD GO STRAIGHT FOR T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I KNEW YOU WOULD GO STRAIGHT FOR THE VILE CAULDRON -- EVERYONE DOES." He does not look surprised. "YOU NEED TO FIRST LEARN ABOUT TYPE A AND B TO APPRECIATE THE DEPRAVITY OF THE CHIMERIC RACES."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "*Maun* is a derogative term for fir..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Maun* is a derogative term for first-world people of Gottwaldian descent. They do not *all* have eczema. Also, people of Katla, like the Suru and the Uuhu, are much more lactose intolerant.

fields.Title: Measurehead's Babe: ""Jean, baby, you're on fire..." The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Jean, baby, you're on fire..." The young woman looks adoringly.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""LESSER RACES LIKE THE *MESQUITO*,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "LESSER RACES LIKE THE *MESQUITO*, A GROTESQUE MIXTURE OF A MESQUE WOMAN AND A SEMENESE MAN, ONLY POSSIBLE IF THE MOTHER IS MESQUE AND THE FATHER SEMENESE. THE OTHER WAY AROUND THEY FAIL TO PRODUCE OFFSPRING."

fields.Title: You: ""Enough of C-F.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Enough of C-F."

fields.Title: Empathy: "He does not seem angry, nor does th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He does not seem angry, nor does the woman look affected. She just twirls her hair. Perhaps they've been through this and established an accord?

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU NEED TO *INTERNALIZE* WHAT YOU..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU NEED TO *INTERNALIZE* WHAT YOU HAVE HEARD HERE TODAY. THEN RETURN TO ME -- THIS CLARITY DOES NOT COME INSTANTLY."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Measurehead: "He turns to you. "YOU COULD HAVE US..."]
Measurehead: ""THE BASIC RACE EDUCATION HE RECEIV..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE BASIC RACE EDUCATION HE RECEIVED IN HIGH SCHOOL HAS LED HIM TO THINK HIS PHYLUM ARE THE SOLE AUTHORS OF RACE THEORY -- AN ESOTERIC STUDY REACHING BACK TO THE ANCIENT MASS SOCIETY OF PERIKARNASSIS, OVER 4,500 YEARS AGO."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Measurehead: "He turns to you. "YOU COULD HAVE US..."]
You: ""I don't know about the rest, but i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know about the rest, but it's clear I should stop drinking the ancient Iilmaraan mind poison Al Gul."

fields.Title: You: ""I imagined a woman, laughing at me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I imagined a woman, laughing at me beneath her pity. Terrible and beautiful."

fields.Title: You: ""I *will* stop drinking.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I *will* stop drinking."

fields.Title: Measurehead's Babe: ""Looks like you're the new Measureh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like you're the new Measurehead now."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "Her voice is surprisingly calm."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her voice is surprisingly calm.

fields.Title: Measurehead's Babe: ""We're gonna miss you, Jean!" The b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're gonna miss you, Jean!" The babes swoon and sigh as if he's about to leave on an interisolary flight.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""RABID ANIMAL, YOU SHOULD BE PUT DO..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "RABID ANIMAL, YOU SHOULD BE PUT DOWN." He releases your poor hand from his grasp. "I WILL NOT BE THE ONE WHO GETS YOUR STINK ON ME."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""I CAN SEE YOU WERE ONCE AN ATHLETE..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I CAN SEE YOU WERE ONCE AN ATHLETE. THEN DETERIORATED IN YOUR TWENTIES. IT IS TYPICAL OF YOUR HAPLOGROUP. LET'S BLAME THE FAILED EDUCATION SYSTEM AND LENIENCY TOWARD DEGENERATES IN YOUR HOMELAND."

fields.Title: You: ""But what *is* Al Gul?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But what *is* Al Gul?"
fields.Alternate1: "Do you mean alcohol?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's not good.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not good."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""OF COURSE YOU ARE, REVACHOLIAN MAN..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "OF COURSE YOU ARE, REVACHOLIAN MAN. THE FAILURE OF COMMUNISM TO CHALLENGE THE WORLD ORDER IS THE CORE OF YOUR RACE FATE. ALL AROUND YOU, THE FRUITS OF ITS DEFEAT: INDIVIDUALISM, ROCK AND ROLL MUSIC, SEXUALLY TRANSMITTED DISEASE..."

fields.Title: You: ""Youth culture does not affect my t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Youth culture does not affect my thinking."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""ROCK AND ROLL IS MORIBUND, ONLY KO..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "ROCK AND ROLL IS MORIBUND, ONLY KOJKOS LISTEN TO IT ANYMORE. THERE IS NO LIFE LEFT IN IT, MY PEOPLE ABANDONED IT LONG AGO. IT LEADS ONLY TO NEUROGENERATIVE HERPES AND HEROIN OVERDOSES."

fields.Title: You: ""I said I'm *not* a communist. I do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I said I'm *not* a communist. I don't know who I am but that's one thing I know."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Measurehead: "Measurehead stoically looks to the..."]
Measurehead: ""YOU SHOULD KEEP HIM CLOSE. THE CON..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU SHOULD KEEP HIM CLOSE. THE CONGENITAL DEFECT OF FARSIGHTEDNESS DOES NOT RENDER HIM A COMPLETE INVALID. HE STILL HAS THE USE OF HIS MIND."

fields.Title: You: ""There's more to it. What have you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's more to it. What have you got against them?"

fields.Title: You: ""The vile C-F race cauldron of pede..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The vile C-F race cauldron of pederasty, please."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""AS PROVEN BY THE MAUN AND THE MESQ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "AS PROVEN BY THE MAUN AND THE MESQUE, OCCIDENTAL TYPE A IS IN RETROGRADE; THE SEMENESE AND THE AREOPAGITE ARE ON THE ASCENT."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""TYPE B ARE THE *UNHEROIC RACES*. A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "TYPE B ARE THE *UNHEROIC RACES*. AMORPHOUS NON-COMPETITORS OF THE GREAT RACE. THE KOJKOS AND THE VACHOLIERS, THEY ARE MUD COLOURED PEOPLE."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THE KOJKO -- THE COUNTLESS MICRONA..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE KOJKO -- THE COUNTLESS MICRONATIONALITIES OF GRAAD -- ARE ALL INEXPLICABLY OBSESSED WITH *POTAAT*. THE ONLY THING THEY LIKE MORE IS DIVIDING INTO MICROSCOPIC ETHNOSTATES. LIKE POLITICAL AMOEBA."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""LOOK, BABE. THE RICH-MAN HAS HUMIL..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "LOOK, BABE. THE RICH-MAN HAS HUMILIATED AND EMASCULATED THIS *COPLET*. HE CAN ONLY THINK IN BASE MATERIALIST CATEGORIES AND FEMININE ABSTRACTIONS LIKE MONEY."

fields.Title: You: ""That's all I wanted.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's all I wanted."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""VERY WELL. YOU MAY ENTER THE DOOR..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "VERY WELL. YOU MAY ENTER THE DOOR *ONCE*." He punches the emergency button with his fist. "OUR RACE CONVERSATION HERE HAS CONCLUDED."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Measurehead: "He turns to you. "YOU COULD HAVE US..."]
Measurehead: "He turns to you. "EFFEMINATE GOSSIP..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He turns to you. "EFFEMINATE GOSSIP-MONGERER, I TAKE PITY ON YOUR TABLOID DRIVEN URGES. YOU CLEARLY WANT TO ENTER THE HARBOUR *BAD*, LIKE A LITTLE BOY WHO WANTS TO GO ON THE POTTY. I CAN PRESS THE BUTTON FOR YOU -- IT WILL OPEN THE DOOR."

fields.Title: You: ""You're wrong. I'll do it. I'm quit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're wrong. I'll do it. I'm quitting!"

fields.Title: Volition: "NO."
fields.Dialogue Text: NO.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "The crackle of bones, inside... you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The crackle of bones, inside... you can hear it.

fields.Title: You: ""Come on, I just need you to move a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Come on, I just need you to move about twenty centimetres back."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""TRUE. I SAID NOTHING ABOUT OUR PER..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "TRUE. I SAID NOTHING ABOUT OUR PERSONAL DYNAMIC -- THAT HAS ALTERED." He adds: "A LITTLE."

fields.Title: You: ""No. I... won't fucking say anythin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I... won't fucking say anything."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Try the jump? Up there, on the roof..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try the jump? Up there, on the roof! It'll be worth it. Else there is little choice but to figure out a way to deal with the man...

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOUR BODY BETRAYS YOUR DEGENERACY.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOUR BODY BETRAYS YOUR DEGENERACY."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THAT IS PRECISELY THE NEGLIGENCE T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THAT IS PRECISELY THE NEGLIGENCE THAT HAS LED YOU TO SUCCUMB TO *AL GUL*." His face contorts in disgust, as if he were smelling a dead rat.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""AL GUL IS AN ANCIENT IILMARAAN POI..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "AL GUL IS AN ANCIENT IILMARAAN POISON, A PARASITIC FUNGUS THAT HAS COLONIZED YOUR RACE. IT IS A TRICK THE DESERT PYGMEES PLAYED ON YOU -- FOR HUMILIATING THEM AND STRIPPING THEM OF THEIR LAND."

fields.Title: You: ""This explains everything.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "This explains everything."

fields.Title: You: ""First, let me make this clear: I'm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "First, let me make this clear: I'm not a drunk. I'm a cop. I just have a drink every now and then, everyone does."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "There is a button right behind him,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is a button right behind him, just out of reach... it must be the one that opens the door to the harbour.

fields.Title: You: ""This is going nowhere." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is going nowhere." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU WILL BE SUPERSEDED -- ISN'T TH..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU WILL BE SUPERSEDED -- ISN'T THAT RIGHT, BABE?"

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOUR RACIAL HERITAGE IS UNINTEREST..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOUR RACIAL HERITAGE IS UNINTERESTING. IT IS THE SAME AS ALL REVACHOLIANS. YOUR PARENTS AND THEIR PARENTS MADE THE DECISION TO REPRODUCE, WHILE UNDER THE INFLUENCE OF AL GUL. THAT IS THE ONLY REASON YOU ARE HERE."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU WILL MAKE DUE WITH YOUR PRIMIT..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU WILL MAKE DUE WITH YOUR PRIMITIVE THEORY. I KNOW THE ANSWER TO THE GREAT RACE ENIGMA. WHY WOULD I SHARE IT WITH A DEFORMED INFANT? YOU DO NOT HAVE THE DEVOTION FOR SERVITUDE."

fields.Title: You: ""Who do you mean?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who do you mean?"

fields.Title: You: ""On second thought, I don't." (Reli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "On second thought, I don't." (Relinquish the opportunity to learn advanced race theory.)

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THERE IS NO OTHER WAY TO ACCOMPLIS..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THERE IS NO OTHER WAY TO ACCOMPLISH ANYTHING. RACECRAFT IS THE ONLY WAY."

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""Okay, got it. Who *are* type A the..."]
Measurehead: ""PINKNESS IS A RACIAL QUALITY THAT..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "PINKNESS IS A RACIAL QUALITY THAT HAS TO BE EARNED THROUGH CENTURIES OF ADVANCED BALLISTIC WARFARE AND CULTURAL DOMINATION THAT THE GRAAD PEOPLE HAVE UNDERGONE FOR DRINKING AL GUL AND SMOKING THE DEGENERATE *TABAC* HERB... AND FOR EATING *POTATO*..."

fields.Title: Logic: "It seems unlikely that two human be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It seems unlikely that two human beings produce genetically sterile offspring.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU ARE RIGHT. YOU *HAVE* MISUNDER..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU ARE RIGHT. YOU *HAVE* MISUNDERSTOOD. YOU LACK BASIC PHYLOGENETIC EDUCATION."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""TO AN UNTRAINED EYE THE KOJKO APPE..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "TO AN UNTRAINED EYE THE KOJKO APPEAR WHITE AND PINKISH. LIKE A HAM SANDWICH. BUT LOOK INTO THEIR EYES AND YOU WILL SEE..." He squints, full of sage wisdom: "THEY ARE OF AN INDISTINCT, MUDDY COLOUR. AND SO IS THEIR SKIN: UNHEALTHY, SWEATY AND ASHEN..."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THAT IS UNDERSTANDABLE. WERE THERE..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THAT IS UNDERSTANDABLE. WERE THERE MORE FORTUNATE TYPES YOU NEEDED TO BE EDUCATED ABOUT?"

fields.Title: Measurehead: "He turns to you. "IMPOTENT SUBJECT..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He turns to you. "IMPOTENT SUBJECT OF POP CULTURE, I TAKE PITY ON YOU. YOU CLEARLY WANT TO ENTER THE HARBOUR BAD -- LIKE A LITTLE BOY WANTS TO GO ON THE POTTY. I CAN PRESS THE BUTTON FOR YOU -- IT WILL OPEN THE DOOR."

fields.Title: You: ""You're wrong. I'll do it. I'm quit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're wrong. I'll do it. I'm quitting!"

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. Who am I kidding. Wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. Who am I kidding. Without party time, grey reality is devoid of reason."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THE UNPROMISING *RACE PUPIL* RETUR..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE UNPROMISING *RACE PUPIL* RETURNS."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU ARE NOT SANTIAGO. SANTIAGO IS..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU ARE NOT SANTIAGO. SANTIAGO IS NOT YOU. EVEN THE PHRENICALLY IMPAIRED CAN SEE THIS."

fields.Title: You: ""Evrart told you to help us get the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Evrart told you to help us get the body down from the tree."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Go ahead, don't be shy. Just ask fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Go ahead, don't be shy. Just ask for race secrets.
fields.Alternate1: Just try again. This is one of those things where the wise sage wants you to exhibit perseverance.

fields.Title: You: ""I knocked you out like a god of ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I knocked you out like a god of martial arts."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Your hand twists in his grip and th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your hand twists in his grip and the pain blinds you. Still you press the words out of your swollen mouth...

fields.Title: Measurehead: "As you slam your fist on the button..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you slam your fist on the button the man collapses entirely, his head rolling to the side...

fields.Title: You: ""The vile C-F race cauldron of pede..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The vile C-F race cauldron of pederasty, please."

fields.Title: Drama: "He had nothing to do with it."
fields.Dialogue Text: He had nothing to do with it.

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah but you still *serve* them. H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah but you still *serve* them. How does that factor into your life?"

fields.Title: Logic: "He means *alcohol*."
fields.Dialogue Text: He means *alcohol*.

fields.Title: You: "Right. Good idea."
fields.Dialogue Text: Right. Good idea.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The drawings are precise and look t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The drawings are precise and look true to their pseudoscientific ambitions. One thing however -- it is not *entirely* free of throwbacks in the phylogenetic tree. His large jaw, for example, could be a trait indicative of criminalism. Also his ear lobes could be smaller.

fields.Title: You: ""Wonderful. We're done with this li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wonderful. We're done with this line of inquiry."

fields.Title: You: ""So you're not really Semenese, you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you're not really Semenese, you're just from Revachol."

fields.Title: You: ""I liked the previous racist better..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I liked the previous racist better, actually."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant does not flinch."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant does not flinch.

fields.Title: You: ""Measurehead, I am new to this worl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Measurehead, I am new to this world. Help me understand its races. I need to know what kind of different races are there?"

fields.Title: Drama: "Yes, it was probably nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, it was probably nothing.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, got it. Who *are* type A the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, got it. Who *are* type A then, in your view?"

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU KNOW THEM BY THE NAMES OF THEI..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU KNOW THEM BY THE NAMES OF THEIR NATION STATES: *THE ORANJESE*, *THE GOTTWALDIANS* AND *THE KÃNIGSTEINERS*. MY PEOPLE SIMPLY CALL THEM *MAUN*."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THE VESPERTINES AND MESSINIANS OF..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THE VESPERTINES AND MESSINIANS OF VESPER AND MESSINA; THE ANCIENT METEORANS OF METEO BY THE GOLDEN PISANTIC SEA, THE SURESNE OF SUR-LA-CLEF AND EVEN THE NORTH-KÃNIGSTEINERS -- ALL HAVE TYPE A RACE PROPENSITIES."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""I KNOW, BABE.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I KNOW, BABE."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Is it 82,000 years that we've been..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is it 82,000 years that we've been recording history? You have very little idea of what is happening, but that seems a little off.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""TYPES C-F ARE A MUSEUM OF FAILED *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "TYPES C-F ARE A MUSEUM OF FAILED *CHIMERIC EXPERIMENTS* AND TRAGIC MAL-ADAPTATIONS. THEY ARE TORTURED CREATURES WAITING TO BE PUT TO SLEEP. YOUR MORBID INTEREST IN THEM WORRIES ME."

fields.Title: You: ""How do I word the Mystery?" (Accep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How do I word the Mystery?" (Accept.)

fields.Title: You: ""This dump is ready to be supersede..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This dump is ready to be superseded by the Areopagite superstate. I can serve as a clerk in your administration -- maybe you need a cop."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""IT IS. BENEATH THE VENEER OF ACADE..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "IT IS. BENEATH THE VENEER OF ACADEMIC JARGON THE LIBERAL THEORIST IS A BEAST, A SEXUAL MANIAC AND A DEPRAVED NIHILIST. LIFE IS A *GAME* TO HIM. WORDS ARE MEANINGLESS. NO ONE IS ACCOUNTABLE FOR ANYTHING."

fields.Title: Measurehead's Babe: ""So un-advanced..." The woman looks..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So un-advanced..." The woman looks half-bored.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""AND, OF COURSE, YOU WILL NOT BE AB..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "AND, OF COURSE, YOU WILL NOT BE ABLE TO FREE YOURSELF FROM THE YOKE OF *GUL*. IT IS TOO LATE. IT MAY BE LETHAL TO STOP AT THIS POINT, BUT STILL..." He pauses in heroic doubt.

fields.Title: Volition: "Your willpower fires up. Directing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your willpower fires up. Directing you to speak...

fields.Title: Measurehead's Babe: ""Jean, baby -- you did the heroic t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Jean, baby -- you did the heroic thing."

fields.Title: Measurehead: "The man looks at you, silent and un..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man looks at you, silent and unmoving. His eyes burrow into the remnants of your soul.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant nods, ready to spend..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant nods, ready to spend some time on his own.

fields.Title: You: ""I also wish I could see it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I also wish I could see it."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We still need to get into the harb..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We still need to get into the harbour. We need help with the tree situation. There must be another way..." His gaze wanders over the Whirling's roof to the yard.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""YOU WILL NOT. YOU CANNOT WITHSTAND..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "YOU WILL NOT. YOU CANNOT WITHSTAND THE WASTE LAND OF REALITY."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Your body does *not* betray your de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your body does *not* betray your degeneracy, that's a lie. You're in great shape.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""IT MUST BE FRIGHTENING TO STAND IN..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "IT MUST BE FRIGHTENING TO STAND IN THE SHADOW OF THIS *RACIAL PINNACLE*. BE CALM, HAM SANDWICH. YOU ARE NOT IN DANGER, BECAUSE YOU ARE NOT A THREAT TO ME."

fields.Title: You: ""So you were born and raised on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you were born and raised on the islands, before you moved to Revachol?"

fields.Title: Measurehead's Babe: ""It is, baby, yeah. You know it!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is, baby, yeah. You know it!"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't have a problem with Al Gul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't have a problem with Al Gul. I just drink a little on the weekends."

fields.Title: Authority: "Show him the ham still got it!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Show him the ham still got it!

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Does this remind you of someone? Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Does this remind you of someone? The guy down there...

fields.Title: You: ""The situation is serious. Your peo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The situation is serious. Your people have probably killed a man. I need to talk to your boss."
fields.Alternate1: "The situation is serious. Your people have probably killed a man."
fields.Alternate2: "It was your people who put that dead body up there. Your people should help me get it down."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "The *best* idea."
fields.Dialogue Text: The *best* idea.

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""DON'T BE VULGAR. WHITE OR NOT HAS..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "DON'T BE VULGAR. WHITE OR NOT HAS GOT LITTLE TO DO WITH THIS. THE *RACE ENIGMA* RUNS MUCH DEEPER THAN THAT." He turns his eyes towards the harbour, seemingly bored with you.

fields.Title: You: ""We're just trying to keep things f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're just trying to keep things from going to shit."

fields.Title: You: ""That's none of your business.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's none of your business."

fields.Title: You: ""Wonderful. I need to enter the har..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wonderful. I need to enter the harbour now -- on police business."
fields.Alternate1: "Wonderful. I need to enter the harbour now -- or you could take the body down yourself maybe?"

fields.Title: You: ""Interesting -- so one of my ancest..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Interesting -- so one of my ancestors was Sur-La-Clef and the other Vesper?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks toward the har..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks toward the harbour's electronic door and then to you. He lets out an audible sigh.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "You're welcome."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're welcome.

fields.Title: You: ""And who are the Semenese and Areop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And who are the Semenese and Areopagites in this?"

fields.Title: You: ""And the Semenese are...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And the Semenese are..."

fields.Title: You: ""Weren't the Iilmaraans pillaged by..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Weren't the Iilmaraans pillaged by *my people* and then Al Gul happened and all that?"

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""NO, THOSE WERE SCIMITAR WIELDING R..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "NO, THOSE WERE SCIMITAR WIELDING RACE LOSERS OF SAHRAVA, YEESUT AND BASHIR, WITH THEIR HIMI SERVANTS. *BIG DIFFERENCE*. THE AREOPAGITES WERE FASTING AND CONQUERING WHILE THIS HAPPENED -- YOU NEVER PENETRATED THE WESTERN DUNES."

fields.Title: You: ""That Revolution sounds like it was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That Revolution sounds like it was perpetrated by degenerate marauders. Not all the people of Revachol."
fields.Alternate1: "That Revolution was perpetrated by degenerate left wing marauders. Not all the people of Revachol."

fields.Title: You: ""Chimeric experiments?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Chimeric experiments?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Wasn't she called *Katya*. A common..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wasn't she called *Katya*. A common name among the...

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""LOST DOE, BUCKLED AWAY AT THE LAST..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "LOST DOE, BUCKLED AWAY AT THE LAST GATE -- THIS IS WHY YOUR HAPLOGROUP WILL NEVER RISE FROM THE ASHES. NOW -- I NEED TO LUXURIATE IN THE PRIVATE COMPANY OF MY BABE. LEAVE ME."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't need your button. I will e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't need your button. I will enter the harbour on my own terms." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Measurehead: "He turns to you. "DEGENERATE SOCIAL..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He turns to you. "DEGENERATE SOCIAL DEMOCRAT, I TAKE PITY ON YOU. YOU CLEARLY WANT TO ENTER THE HARBOUR BAD. LIKE A LITTLE BOY WHO WANTS TO GO ON THE POTTY. I CAN PRESS THE BUTTON FOR YOU -- IT WILL OPEN THE DOOR."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""TAKE SOLACE FROM THE FACT THAT THE..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "TAKE SOLACE FROM THE FACT THAT THESE THOUGHTS..." He points to your head. "WILL *NEVER* ENTIRELY LEAVE YOUR BRAIN. THEY WILL BE WITH YOU ON THE DAY YOU DIE -- THE ONLY GERM OF HEROISM IN YOUR BODY. NOW GO, I HAVE BEAUTY AND TRUTH TO DISCUSS WITH MY WOMAN."

fields.Title: You: ""I imagined the pyknic face of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I imagined the pyknic face of the desert pygmee laughing at me, crooked teeth grinning."

fields.Title: Measurehead: ""THAT IS NOT POSSIBLE. THE GAME OF..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "THAT IS NOT POSSIBLE. THE GAME OF *SHAH-MAT* YOU PLAY AGAINST THE GUL'S TRICKS IS UNWINNABLE. THE DAYS, THE WEEKS, THE MONTHS WILL WEAR YOU OUT. THE OCCIDENTAL HAPLOGROUP IS INCAPABLE OF LONG TERM LUCID THOUGHT."

fields.Title: Authority: "He means *very* little."
